        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:27PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles north of Ashland, or 18 miles east of Colstrip, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Brandenberg.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
